const PI = 3.14;

What is the difference between var and let?
  var hoisting, function scoped, can redeclare.
  let is block scoped, can't redeclare, no hoisting.
What is the difference between var and const?
  var hoisting, function scoped, can redeclare, can mutate.
  const is block scoped, can't redeclare, no hoisting, can't mutate.
What is the difference between let and const?
  can't mutate
What is hoisting?
  variable is declared before code executed, prevents errors when calling undeclared variables in normal execution of code. 
